      <p>Origin is one of the most significant factors in a Blue Sapphire's value. Two stones that look similar can differ enormously in price based on where they came from — and that origin should always be disclosed and lab-verified for premium pieces.</p>
      <p>Beyond origin, price is shaped by colour depth and saturation, treatment status (untreated stones command a premium), clarity, cut quality, and size. A smaller stone with commanding colour and natural stability will outperform a larger, dull one.</p>
