      <p style="margin-top: 16px;">Australian Opals are more stable, durable, and the clear preference for astrological wear. Ethiopian Opals are visually striking and more accessible in price, but they are hydrophane — meaning they absorb moisture and can turn temporarily cloudy with water exposure.</p>
