      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Is White Sapphire a replacement for Diamond?</strong>
        <p>Yes, in Vedic astrology, White Sapphire is the primary and most effective "Upratana" or alternative to Diamond.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Does it look like a Diamond?</strong>
        <p>It has high brilliance but lacks the specific "fire" or rainbows of a diamond, appearing more composed and white.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Which origin is best?</strong>
        <p>Sri Lankan (Ceylon) White Sapphires are the world's finest for their lack of yellow or grey undertones.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Can it be worn on the ring finger?</strong>
        <p>Yes, it is often worn on the ring or middle finger for Venus remedies.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'red-coral' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Why does some coral have small holes?</strong>
        <p>Natural corals are organic and may have tiny pores or grain marks. "Clean" corals without these are rarer and more expensive.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Is Italian coral better than Japanese?</strong>
        <p>Italian coral is the benchmark for astrological use due to its density and deep red colour, while Japanese coral is rarer and even more prized.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Can Red Coral be worn by anyone?</strong>
        <p>No. Mars is a powerful planet. It is strongly advised to check if your horoscope is Mangalik or has a favourable Mars position.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which metal is best?</strong>
        <p>Gold or Copper-alloy (Panchdhatu) is recommended for Red Coral.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'pearl' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>What is a "Basra" Pearl?</strong>
        <p>Basra pearls are natural, wild pearls from the Persian Gulf. They are extremely rare, historic, and highly sought after for astrology.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Do you sell real pearls?</strong>
        <p>Yes. We provide Natural, South Sea, and high-quality Freshwater pearls, all certified for authenticity.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Why did my pearl turn yellow?</strong>
        <p>Pearls are organic and can absorb sweat or oils over years. Regular wiping after wear helps maintain their lustre.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which metal is best for Pearl?</strong>
        <p>Silver is the best metal for Pearl to enhance its cooling and calming properties.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'hessonite' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>What colour is best for Gomed?</strong>
        <p>The "Honey" or "Amber" colour (resembling a cow's urine) is traditionally considered most effective for Rahu.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Which origin is best?</strong>
        <p>Sri Lankan (Ceylon) Hessonite is superior for its lack of black or "muddy" inclusions.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Who should wear Gomed?</strong>
        <p>Those undergoing Rahu Mahadasha or those in fields like politics, gambling, or high-risk business, after consultation.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which metal is best?</strong>
        <p>Silver is generally preferred for Hessonite.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'cats-eye' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>What is the difference between Quartz and Chrysoberyl Cat's Eye?</strong>
        <p>Chrysoberyl is much rarer and harder. For Ketu remedies, Chrysoberyl is the primary and most powerful stone.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>What determines the quality of the "eye"?</strong>
        <p>A sharp, straight, and mobile line (chatoyancy) that opens and closes is the sign of a top-quality Lehsunia.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Can Cat's Eye be worn long-term?</strong>
        <p>Usually, it is worn for specific remedial periods or durante Ketu dasha. Regular evaluation by an astrologer is advised.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which metal is best?</strong>
        <p>Silver is traditionally preferred for Cat's Eye.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'amethyst' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>How is Amethyst related to Neelam?</strong>
        <p>Amethyst (Jamuniya) is the primary "Upratana" for Blue Sapphire, offering similar Saturn energy but with much less intensity.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Does Amethyst fade?</strong>
        <p>Yes, long exposure to direct, intense sunlight can cause the purple colour to fade over time. Store in a cool, shaded place.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Can I wear it for protection?</strong>
        <p>Yes, it is widely used as a protective stone against negative habits and for mental sobriety.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'citrine' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Is Citrine a replacement for Pukhraj?</strong>
        <p>Yes, Citrine (Sunela) is a popular and effective alternative to Yellow Sapphire for Jupiter-related benefits.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Is natural Citrine rare?</strong>
        <p>Yes, most citrine in the market is heat-treated amethyst. We provide natural, earth-mined citrine for astrological use.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which metal is best?</strong>
        <p>Silver or Gold can both be used for Citrine depending on the desired intensity of the remedy.</p>
      </div>
    {%- when 'turquoise' -%}
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>Is Turquoise (Firoza) suitable for daily wear?</strong>
        <p>It is porous and sensitive. It should be worn carefully and kept away from oils, lotions, and soaps.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-bottom: 20px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;">
        <strong>What is the "matrix" in Turquoise?</strong>
        <p>The matrix is the webbing of brown or black host rock. While some prefer clean blue, "Spiderweb" matrix is also highly valued.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Which origin is most famous?</strong>
        <p>Nishapur (Iran) and Sleeping Beauty (Arizona) are the most historic and prized origins for Turquoise.</p>
      </div>
  {%- endcase -%}
{%- endcapture -%}

{%- comment -%} Check if we have mapped content for this collection {%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign has_mapped_content = false -%}
{%- capture handles -%}emerald,blue-sapphire,opal,ruby,yellow-sapphire,white-sapphire,red-coral,pearl,hessonite,cats-eye,amethyst,citrine,turquoise{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign handle_list = handles | split: "," -%}
{%- for handle in handle_list -%}
  {%- if gem_handle == handle -%}
    {%- assign has_mapped_content = true -%}
    {%- break -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}

<!-- Breadcrumb — above hero -->
<div class="cht-breadcrumb">
  <div class="page-width">
    <nav class="cht-breadcrumb__nav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="cht-breadcrumb__link">Home</a>
      <span class="cht-breadcrumb__sep">|</span>
      {%- if collection.metafields.custom.parent_collection_title != blank -%}
        <a href="{{ collection.metafields.custom.parent_collection | default: '/collections' }}" class="cht-breadcrumb__link">{{ collection.metafields.custom.parent_collection_title }}</a>
        <span class="cht-breadcrumb__sep">|</span>
      {%- elsif collection.handle contains 'ruby' or collection.handle contains 'emerald' or collection.handle contains 'sapphire' or collection.handle contains 'pearl' or collection.handle contains 'coral' or collection.handle contains 'hessonite' or collection.handle contains 'cats-eye' or collection.handle contains 'opal' -%}
        <a href="/collections" class="cht-breadcrumb__link">Navratans</a>
        <span class="cht-breadcrumb__sep">|</span>
      {%- endif -%}
      <span class="cht-breadcrumb__current">{{ collection.title }}</span>
    </nav>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="collection-hero-tabs" id="CollectionHeroTabs-{{ section.id }}">
  <!-- 1. Split Hero Section -->
  <div class="collection-hero">
    <div class="collection-hero__lifestyle">
      {%- if lifestyle_img -%}
        <img src="{{ lifestyle_img | image_url: width: 1200 }}" alt="{{ collection.title }}" loading="lazy">
      {%- elsif collection.image -%}
        <img src="{{ collection.image | image_url: width: 1200 }}" alt="{{ collection.title }}" loading="lazy">
      {%- else -%}
        <img src="{{ 'collection-default-page.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Gemstone collection placeholder" loading="lazy">
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    <div class="collection-hero__info">
      <div class="collection-hero__info-inner">
        {%- assign _icon_asset = 'nav-' | append: collection.handle | append: '.png' -%}
        
        <h1 class="collection-hero__title">{{ collection.title | default: "Featured Collection" }}</h1>

        {%- if hero_tagline != blank -%}
          <p class="collection-hero__tagline">{{ hero_tagline }}</p>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if summary != blank -%}
          <div class="collection-hero__description">
            {{ summary | strip_html | truncatewords: 60 }}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}

        <ul class="collection-hero__benefits">
          {%- assign benefit_lines = benefits | split: "\n" -%}
          {%- for line in benefit_lines -%}
            {%- if line != blank -%}
              <li>{{ line | prepend: "• " }}</li>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 2. Tabbed Content Section -->
  <div class="collection-tabs-wrapper">
    <div class="page-width">
      <nav class="collection-tabs" aria-label="Collection tabs">
        <ul class="collection-tabs__list" role="tablist">
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="about">ABOUT</button>
          </li>
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="who-wear">WHO SHOULD WEAR</button>
          </li>
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="benefits">BENEFITS</button>
          </li>
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="pricing">PRICING</button>
          </li>
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="care-guide">CARE GUIDE</button>
          </li>
          <li class="collection-tabs__item">
            <button class="collection-tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="faq">FAQ</button>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <div class="collection-tabs__panels">
        <!-- Panel 1: ABOUT -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-about" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">About {{ collection.title }}</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_about != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_about }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_about }}
            {%- else -%}
              <p>Welcome to our exclusive {{ collection.title }} collection. At Precious Carats, we understand that a gemstone is not just a piece of jewelry; it is a repository of planetary energy and a bridge between the celestial and the earthly. Our {{ collection.title }} selection is meticulously curated for their exceptional "Sattvic" qualities—ensuring every stone is pure, vibrant, and ready to serve its astrological purpose.</p>
              <p>Each stone in this collection has been hand-selected by our master gemologists based on its color saturation, clarity, and most importantly, its vibrant internal "fire" which indicates high energy potency. Whether you are a collector or seeking a stone for Vedic remedial purposes, our {{ collection.title }} offer the perfect balance of aesthetic beauty and spiritual depth.</p>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Panel 2: WHO SHOULD WEAR -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-who-wear" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">Who Should Wear</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_who_wear != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_who_wear }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_who_wear }}
            {%- else -%}
              <p>In the sacred science of Vedic Astrology (Jyotish), {{ collection.title }} are traditionally associated with specific planetary vibrations. While generic recommendations exist, the power of a gemstone is best harnessed when aligned with your unique birth chart (Kundli).</p>
              <div style="background: #fdfaf5; padding: 25px; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold); margin: 20px 0;">
                <strong>General Guidelines:</strong>
                <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                  <li><strong>Ascendants:</strong> Typically recommended for specific Zodiac signs based on the planetary position of their ruling lord.</li>
                  <li><strong>Mahadasha:</strong> Individuals currently undergoing the planetary period (Dasha) of the associated planet may find significant relief and growth.</li>
                  <li><strong>Life Goals:</strong> Highly recommended for those seeking to enhance their authority, mental clarity, or creative expression in professional fields.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p><em>*We strongly advise consulting with a qualified Vedic Astrologer to ensure the stone is compatible with your horoscope before wearing.</em></p>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Panel 3: BENEFITS -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-benefits" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">The Power & Benefits of {{ collection.title }}</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_benefits != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_benefits }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_benefits }}
            {%- else -%}
              <p>Wearing an authentic, energized {{ collection.title }} is believed to transmit cosmic rays directly into the human body, influencing the subtle energy centers (Chakras). Key benefits associated with this collection include:</p>
              <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">
                <div>
                  <h4 style="color: #1a3c34; margin-bottom: 10px;">✨ Spiritual & Mental</h4>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Enhances concentration and focus during meditation.</li>
                    <li>Promotes a sense of calm and emotional stability.</li>
                    <li>Boosts self-confidence and removes deep-seated fears.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h4 style="color: #1a3c34; margin-bottom: 10px;">🏆 Success & Growth</h4>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Attracts opportunities for professional advancement.</li>
                    <li>Improves decision-making and leadership capabilities.</li>
                    <li>Removes hurdles in financial and creative pursuits.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Panel 4: PRICING -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-pricing" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">The Value & Pricing of {{ collection.title }}</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_pricing != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_pricing }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_pricing }}
            {%- else -%}
              <p>The pricing for fine {{ collection.title }} is multifaceted and determined by the rarity of its natural characteristics. Unlike mass-produced goods, every gemstone in our vault is a unique creation of nature.</p>
              <table style="width: 100%; margin-top: 20px; border-collapse: collapse;">
                <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
                  <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee; text-align: left;">Factor</th>
                  <th style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee; text-align: left;">Impact on Value</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;"><strong>Origin</strong></td>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;">Premium origins (e.g., Ceylon, Burma, Colombia) command higher prices due to historic rarity.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;"><strong>Color</strong></td>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;">The "Vivid" or "Royal" shades with balanced saturation are the most prized.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;"><strong>Treatment</strong></td>
                  <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #eee;">Completely Unheated stones are significantly more valuable than heat-treated ones.</td>
                </tr>
              </table>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Panel 5: CARE GUIDE -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-care-guide" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">Preserving Your Gemstone’s Energy</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_care_guide != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_care_guide }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_care_guide }}
            {%- else -%}
              <p>To ensure your {{ collection.title }} continues to radiate positive energy and maintain its physical brilliance, a balanced care routine is essential.</p>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">🧼 Physical Cleaning</h4>
              <p>Clean your gemstone once a month using a soft brush and a solution of mild, phosphate-free dish soap in lukewarm water. Gently scrub the underside where dust often accumulates. Rinse with filtered water and pat dry with a lint-free cloth.</p>
              <h4 style="margin-top: 20px;">🌙 Spiritual Cleansing (Energization)</h4>
              <p>To remove accumulated negative vibes, place your gemstone in a bowl of pure rock salt or leave it under the soft light of a full moon overnight. This refreshes the stone's natural vibrations.</p>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Panel 6: FAQ -->
        <div class="collection-tabs__panel" id="tab-faq" role="tabpanel">
          <h2 class="collection-tabs__panel-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <div class="collection-tabs__panel-content rte">
            {%- if collection.metafields.custom.content_faq != blank -%}
              {{ collection.metafields.custom.content_faq }}
            {%- elsif has_mapped_content -%}
              {{ mapped_faq }}
            {%- else -%}
              <div style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <strong>Are these stones Lab-Grown?</strong>
                <p>No. We deal exclusively in 100% natural, earth-mined gemstones. We do not sell synthetic or "lab-grown" alternatives.</p>
              </div>
              <div style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                <strong>How do I know the stone is authentic?</strong>
                <p>Every single gemstone in this collection comes with an independent lab certificate from a government-recognized gemological laboratory confirming its natural status and origin.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <strong>Is the stone already energized?</strong>
                <p>Yes, all our stones undergo a traditional Vedic "Pran-Pratishtha" or energization process at a holy shrine before they are shipped to ensure they are active for remedial purposes.</p>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

